1
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:36,320
How is it? Has his temperature gone down?

2
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:37,560
No, Brother Pang.

3
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:38,159
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

4
00:00:38,159 --> 00:00:39,719
Mr. Lu, don't let him burn up.

5
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:41,320
Okay, okay.

6
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,159
Wipe his palms and forehead.

7
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:50,640
Old Lu, we're out of gauze.

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,759
Okay, okay, coming.

9
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:06,799
Listen.

10
00:01:07,159 --> 00:01:08,040
What's that sound?

11
00:01:08,319 --> 00:01:09,000
What sound?

12
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:11,840
It's hornets.

13
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:12,640
Hornets?

14
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,959
Hor... hornets.

15
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,439
Why is it those things again?

16
00:01:16,799 --> 00:01:18,400
We haven't run into anything else since we entered Southern Yunnan.

17
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:19,359
It's fine.

18
00:01:19,359 --> 00:01:20,799
Didn't we deal with them last time?

19
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:21,920
Bring the flare.

20
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:24,159
I gave all my flares to you guys last time.

21
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,879
We used ours up too.

22
00:01:27,079 --> 00:01:28,599
Good thing I'm here.

23
00:01:28,959 --> 00:01:29,879
I still have one here.

24
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:30,519
Dawei.

25
00:01:30,599 --> 00:01:32,239
Cover Old Chen completely with banana leaves.

26
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,359
Old Lu, stand in the center.

27
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,000
The enemy is at eleven o'clock.

28
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,200
Brother Pang.

29
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,359
Brother Pang, Brother Pang, Brother Pang!

30
00:01:38,359 --> 00:01:39,680
There are some at two o'clock too.

31
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:41,680
Old Lu.

32
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,280
We only have one flare.

33
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,120
Just this one.

34
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:46,840
Don't pull the pin until you see the rabbit.

35
00:01:49,799 --> 00:01:51,280
I said don't pull the pin.

36
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,400
Didn't you say pull the pin?

37
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,439
Don't pull the pin until you see the rabbit.

38
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:57,519
Then why did you say pull the pin?

39
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:59,799
It's good to build up some courage first.

40
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:00,519
Right?

41
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,640
They haven't come yet.

42
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,079
Eleven o'clock.

43
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,519
Two... two o'clock, two o'clock.

44
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,840
Eleven o'clock.

45
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:07,840
Two o'clock.

46
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,520
Over here.

47
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,919
Over here, Mr. Lu.

48
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,360
Twelve o'clock.

49
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,400
I'll hide behind you.

50
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,520
Mr. Lu, help me out, quick.

51
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:00,879
Cover Old Chen up.

52
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,719
I'll cover you.

53
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:07,000
Where's our propane tank?

54
00:03:07,759 --> 00:03:08,199
Propane tank?

55
00:03:08,199 --> 00:03:10,039
Wasn't it lost along with the medical kit?

56
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:11,400
Why bring that up?

57
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:14,479
I've never missed that bastard Huang Long so much.

58
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:16,479
It'd be great if he were here.

59
00:03:16,479 --> 00:03:18,520
One explosion and it'd be over.

60
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:21,039
No, I can't wave it anymore.

61
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,639
Fatty.

62
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,639
Staff Officer He.

63
00:03:40,039 --> 00:03:40,680
Prepare to shoot.

64
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,439
Here they come.

65
00:03:48,159 --> 00:03:49,159
Good job, Staff Officer He.

66
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:50,759
Another one.

67
00:03:51,039 --> 00:03:52,000
Ready, good.

68
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,199
This really works.

69
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,919
Nice shooting.

70
00:04:02,199 --> 00:04:03,000
They're all gone.

71
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,120
Oh my god.

72
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:07,120
Staff Officer He is back.

73
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,240
How is Chen Youxi?

74
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:10,639
His high fever won't go down.

75
00:04:10,639 --> 00:04:11,639
Move the tent away.

76
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,000
He's still so hot.

77
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:24,959
Isn't this our medical kit?

78
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,319
You found it.

79
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,560
Old Chen really is lucky.

80
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,480
He's saved now.

81
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,000
Unbuckle his belt.

82
00:04:39,319 --> 00:04:40,519
Have him take these two pills.

83
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,360
The pus has mostly been absorbed.

84
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,879
Give me the gauze and tape.

85
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,480
Scissors.

86
00:05:12,439 --> 00:05:14,920
Next time this happens, tell us earlier.

87
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,639
You almost lost your life, you know?

88
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,800
But I've got you, haven't I?

89
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,839
Don't let it happen again.

90
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,000
Glad you can still joke around.

91
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,319
Thank goodness.

92
00:05:25,319 --> 00:05:27,360
Alright, stop thanking the gods.

93
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,560
If you want to thank someone, thank ourselves.

94
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,519
No, no.

95
00:05:30,839 --> 00:05:32,399
We mainly have to thank Staff Officer He.

96
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:33,920
For finding this first aid kit.

97
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,000
That's a great contribution.

98
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,959
I didn't find this kit.

99
00:05:37,959 --> 00:05:40,079
I ran into miasma on my way there.

100
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:42,079
When I woke up, the kit was right next to me.

101
00:05:42,079 --> 00:05:43,319
I don't know who brought it over.

102
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:46,800
You didn't find this kit?

103
00:05:48,319 --> 00:05:49,480
That's strange.

104
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,560
That means...

105
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,160
we're not the only ones in this forest.

106
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:54,600
There are other people here.

107
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:56,800
Old Chen.

108
00:05:57,319 --> 00:05:59,079
We're out in the open, and they're in the dark.

109
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,639
That's not a good thing.

110
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,519
Yeah.

111
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,240
First,

112
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,959
who they are and how many of them there are,

113
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
we can't tell.

114
00:06:07,519 --> 00:06:08,199
Second,

115
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:10,800
this action of theirs wasn't malicious.

116
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,800
It saved my life.

117
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,680
Of course, we can't rule out the possibility of an ulterior motive.

118
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,759
We just have to stay alert.

119
00:06:17,879 --> 00:06:18,879
Stay sharp.

120
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:23,000
Why did those Nan Yun Giant Black Hornets come back?

121
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,000
It is very strange.

122
00:06:24,079 --> 00:06:25,879
A swarm as big as that one just now,

123
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:26,759
it's my first time seeing it too.

124
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:27,959
There were even more than last time.

125
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,160
Fatty.

126
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,079
Do you still have garlic?

127
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:33,319
You like that stuff too?

128
00:06:33,319 --> 00:06:34,399
Don't eat it now.

129
00:06:34,399 --> 00:06:35,120
You two are so close to each other,

130
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,800
Old Chen will be disgusted by you later.

131
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,000
I'm not joking with you.

132
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,199
It's not for eating.

133
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,519
I get it.

134
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:44,959
But this is a different place.

135
00:06:45,439 --> 00:06:48,040
I can understand bringing black donkey hooves and glutinous rice.

136
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,439
But your Western style,

137
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,639
using garlic to ward off vampires,

138
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,120
it's not the same system.

139
00:06:52,439 --> 00:06:54,240
I heard there's a local folk remedy in Southern Yunnan.

140
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,879
Mash garlic and Siam weed into juice,

141
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:57,720
and rub it on the skin.

142
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,000
It can be used to repel bees.

143
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,519
No,

144
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:01,759
you've studied abroad so much,

145
00:07:01,759 --> 00:07:03,839
how can you still believe in folk remedies curing big diseases?

146
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,120
Our combat power isn't enough.

147
00:07:05,199 --> 00:07:06,319
Better safe than sorry.

148
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,639
There's no other way right now.

149
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,240
In such a short time,

150
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,680
we've been attacked by Nan Yun Giant Black Hornets twice.

151
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,319
Their nest must be nearby.

152
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:20,720
This is bad.

153
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:21,639
Old Chen.

154
00:07:21,879 --> 00:07:23,519
You just woke up, why did you have to say that?

155
00:07:23,519 --> 00:07:24,319
Jinx.

156
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,079
Th-They're here.

157
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,199
Even more than before.

158
00:07:27,519 --> 00:07:28,120
Go, go, go!

159
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:28,920
Go, hurry!

160
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:30,160
Go!

161
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,079
Old Chen, you just got a bit better.

162
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,160
Can you make it?

163
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:36,600
Let me see. Hurry!

164
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,800
You guys keep up!

165
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,120
Wait,

166
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,160
why are these giant bees changing formation?

167
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,519
Doctor,

168
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,279
tell us what's going on!

169
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,639
I don't know either!

170
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,800
They're just insects after all.

171
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,680
They can't be highly intelligent creatures, right?

172
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,319
Why are they coming in formation?

173
00:07:50,319 --> 00:07:51,079
This is...

174
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,560
This damn thing.

175
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:56,360
What do we do? What do we do?

176
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,600
Comrades!

177
00:07:57,839 --> 00:07:58,639
Get in the water!

178
00:07:59,079 --> 00:07:59,759
Okay, okay, okay!

179
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,319
This water is freezing!

180
00:08:01,319 --> 00:08:01,879
Hurry!

181
00:08:01,879 --> 00:08:02,839
It's freezing! Go!

182
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:04,439
Who cares if it's freezing? Hurry!

183
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,160
I can't do it!

184
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:05,920
Jump together!

185
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,720
One, two, three!

186
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,600
Old Lu, slow down.

187
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,519
I'll slow down.

188
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,320
They're gone.

189
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,120
Those giant bees are all gone.

190
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,200
Gone.

191
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,200
What's going on?

192
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,799
The water is rising!

193
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,320
It's massive!

194
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,039
Get ashore, quick!

195
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:54,080
Look over there! Let's go!

196
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:01,600
Old Lu!

197
00:09:01,799 --> 00:09:02,600
Give me your hand!

198
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,320
Come on!

199
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,039
Hurry up!

200
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:13,440
Quick!

201
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,159
Chen Youxi!

202
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:25,519
Old Chen!

203
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:26,360
Brother!

204
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:30,240
Grab my hand! Quick!

205
00:09:41,919 --> 00:09:43,080
Give me your other hand too!

206
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:43,960
Quick!

207
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:46,720
Hurry!

208
00:09:58,519 --> 00:09:59,840
You have to hold on!

209
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,000
Let go!

210
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:01,759
Come here!

211
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,440
I won't let go!

212
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,399
Or we'll both be washed away!

213
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,559
Let go!

214
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:12,200
Even if I die, I'm dying with you!

215
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,279
Chen Youxi!

216
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,799
Let go, quick!

217
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,519
Old Chen!

218
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:30,519
Brother!

219
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,559
Chen Youxi!

220
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:27,840
Chen Youxi!

221
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:34,320
Chen Youxi! Chen Youxi!

222
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,039
Chen Youxi!

223
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:44,120
Shutong!

224
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:47,440
Shutong!

225
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:48,679
Chen Youxi!

226
00:11:50,759 --> 00:11:52,679
Old Chen! Old Chen!

227
00:11:53,159 --> 00:11:53,919
Old Chen!

228
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,320
Staff Officer He!

229
00:11:56,519 --> 00:11:57,320
Old Chen!

230
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:09,039
What beautiful scenery.

231
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,799
If we weren't out here treasure hunting...

232
00:12:11,799 --> 00:12:12,799
No, no, no.

233
00:12:14,159 --> 00:12:15,000
Doing archaeology.

234
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,480
I really wouldn't want to leave.

235
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,559
How's your arm?

236
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:19,759
Did you bump it just now?

237
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:20,440
It's fine.

238
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,200
Let me see.

239
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,080
Does it hurt here?

240
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,240
It shouldn't be a bone injury.

241
00:12:29,399 --> 00:12:30,679
Just a sprained muscle.

242
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,039
It's nothing.

243
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:34,799
Thank you.

244
00:12:36,159 --> 00:12:37,039
That's rare.

245
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:40,480
I have to say, Staff Officer He is really reliable.

246
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:42,960
I've only seen heroes saving beauties.

247
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,399
First time seeing a beauty save a hero.

248
00:12:45,399 --> 00:12:46,840
Staff Officer He, she is...

249
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,799
A heroine among women.

250
00:12:47,799 --> 00:12:49,240
Like Hua Mulan or Mu Guiying.

251
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,240
Speaking of which...

252
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:52,399
Fatty, if it weren't for your explosion...

253
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,639
The hornets would have swarmed us.

254
00:12:53,639 --> 00:12:55,399
There wouldn't even be bones left of us.

255
00:12:55,799 --> 00:12:56,679
Logically speaking...

256
00:12:56,679 --> 00:12:58,919
It's in the hornets' nature to chase prey.

257
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,240
But for the swarm to be so massive...

258
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,399
And to relentlessly pursue us...

259
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,679
It's too bizarre.

260
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:05,399
Right.

261
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:06,279
Oh boy.

262
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,720
It's like they were organized.

263
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,120
They had a strategy.

264
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:11,279
You're saying these bugs got here...

265
00:13:11,279 --> 00:13:13,240
And suddenly grew brains?

266
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,879
Insects do have brains.

267
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,480
Not only do they have brains...

268
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,519
They also have a complete nervous system.

269
00:13:18,879 --> 00:13:22,000
Their brain functions similarly to a human's.

270
00:13:22,639 --> 00:13:24,720
Both are centers for control and coordination.

271
00:13:25,399 --> 00:13:26,639
Bugs knowing martial arts...

272
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,000
No one can stop them.

273
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,519
That means they have intelligence.

274
00:13:30,279 --> 00:13:33,919
If the queen directed the swarm to attack us...

275
00:13:35,399 --> 00:13:36,559
What was the purpose?

276
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:38,360
Normally speaking...

277
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,720
As long as humans don't invade their hives...

278
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,759
They won't actively attack humans.

279
00:13:45,279 --> 00:13:46,120
Big Fatty.

280
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:48,399
It must be you, going behind our backs...

281
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,519
To steal their honey.

282
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:51,519
And ended up making enemies, right?

283
00:13:51,799 --> 00:13:52,960
Cut it out.

284
00:13:53,639 --> 00:13:55,200
Do you think I'm a black bear?

285
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,399
Why would I steal honey?

286
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:57,799
Besides...

287
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,799
When have you ever seen me act alone?

288
00:13:59,919 --> 00:14:01,919
Then what's the real reason?

289
00:14:02,919 --> 00:14:04,240
There's another possibility.

290
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,519
Someone is playing tricks in the dark.

291
00:14:07,399 --> 00:14:08,639
And lured the swarm here.

292
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:10,960
Right.

293
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,240
What kind of person is this?

294
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,720
If you say they're a good person...

295
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,200
They did give us medicine.

296
00:14:15,519 --> 00:14:16,720
But after giving us the medicine...

297
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,799
They got a bunch of giant hornets to chase and sting us.

298
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,720
Isn't this...

299
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,000
Isn't this completely messed up?

300
00:14:23,759 --> 00:14:24,799
Could it be...

301
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,639
That more than one person is following us?
